![medium](https://www.gstatic.com/codereviewagent/medium-priority.svg)

Refactor the retry loop to avoid duplicating the `repository.create` call. Using a `while (true)` loop with an explicit counter keeps the compiler happy and eliminates the redundant call outside the loop.

```kotlin
        var attempts = 0
        while (true) {
            try {
                return repository.create(uniqueName(base), spec)
            } catch (e: SQLiteConstraintException) {
                if (++attempts >= CREATE_UNIQUE_NAME_MAX_ATTEMPTS) throw e
                // Name taken since the check; recompute against current rows.
            }
        }
```

![medium](https://www.gstatic.com/codereviewagent/medium-priority.svg)

Use `mergeDescendants = true` in the `semantics` block to ensure that the key button is treated as a single accessibility element, cleanly reading the `contentDescription` without double-announcing or reading the raw symbol text, while preserving click action semantics.

```suggestion
        .let {
            if (contentDescription != null && text != null) {
                it.semantics(mergeDescendants = true) { this.contentDescription = contentDescription }
            } else {
                it
            }
        }
```

